<div class="property-location">
<p>Ashford was home to the first High Speed rail link in the UK, connecting the town with London St Pancras in 36 minutes and 29 to London Stratford. It is also a major terminus for Eurostar, directly connected to three European capitals; Brussels in 1h 32 mins, Paris in 1h 52 mins and Amsterdam in 3hrs 50 mins.</p>

<p>With a 24% growth in population over 20 years to 2031, it is one of the fastest growing populations in the south east, a trend only increased by the pandemic as people search for space outside of London, whilst also being unwilling to compromise on commute. Ashford offers both hence why it is presents an attractive UK property investment opportunity.</p>

<p>Attracting a growing number of businesses because of its low employee costs and excellent international rail connection to Europe, has had a knock-on effect on its housing market with strong demand for new homes, from both the local marketing and those migrating to Ashford.
</p>

<p>Ashford has undergone intensive investment and regeneration to its public infrastructure, including a new completed motorway junction and more recently the approval of a mixed-use estate to create a world class film studio over 240,000 sq ft. Its designer shopping village recently completed a £90 million extension; home to over 130 premium brands.</p>
